                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                                                          Beckham academy shuts down
    Carson: The David Beckham Academy, in Carson and another location in Britain has closed, although the Los Angeles Galaxy star is working to develop another soccer coaching programme for children. Both camps were jointly run by Anschutz Entertainment Group, which owns the Galaxy, and 19 Entertainment, Beckham rsquo;s management team. AEG said Monday that the Carson location was closed before Christmas. Beckham rsquo;s website said the lease on the location in Greenwich, England, had expired.  Appeal off
    Manchester: Rio Ferdinand has withdrawn his appeal against a four-game ban which the Manchester United defender received after elbowing Hull rsquo;s Craig Fagan. The FA had effectively added an extra game to the usual three-match ban because Ferdinand contested the charge of violent conduct, a defence which was dismissed as ldquo;frivolous rdquo;.  Left out
    Sao Paulo: Coach Dunga has left out Ronaldinho for Brazil rsquo;s final friendly before the World Cup despite pressure from fans and local media to select the star midfielder. Ronaldinho was not among the 22 players called up by Dunga on Tuesday for Brazil rsquo;s friendly against Ireland in London on March 2.  Abidal injury
    Barcelona: Barcelona defender Eric Abidal has a leg injury and is likely to be sidelined for up to eight weeks.  Heat ban
    Rio de Janeiro: The intense heat in southern Brazil this month has led a judge in the state of Rio Grande do Sul to issue a ban on football matches when the temperature exceeds 35 degrees Celsius.  Milan sponsor
    Milan: The Dubai government-owned Emirates airline is to sponsor AC Milan from next season in a four-year shirt deal worth around euros 50 million, a source close to the Italian club said on Monday.  Prakash loses
    Bergamo: The Indian challenge in singles at the euro 425,000 ATP Challenger event ended with the first round defeat of Prakash Amritraj. The unseeded Indian went down 5-7, 6-1, 5-7 to wild card Marco Crugnola in the opening round. The doubles will see Prakash and Harsh Mankad competing with their respective partners.   PCB probe
    Karachi: Pakistan all-rounder Shahid Afridi will appear before a six-member inquiry committee on Friday to explain his ball biting antic in Perth, while captain Mohammed Yousuf and coach Intikhab Alam would depose with their versions of the team rsquo;s comprehensive rout in Australia.
    Dipika dismay
    New Delhi: Dipika Pallikal rsquo;s dream run in the Swedish Squash Open came to an end as she lost to Annelize Naude of the Netherlands in straight frames in the semi-final in Linkoping. Pallikal, seeded third, lost 9-11, 8-11, 12-14 in 30 minutes Monday.
                                                                                                                                                            
